---
import founderOne from '../assets/founder-1.png';
---

<section class="overflow-hidden bg-white px-5 py-20 lg:px-8 lg:py-28">
	<div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_0.95fr] lg:items-center">
		<div class="relative min-h-[620px]">
			<div class="absolute -left-5 top-10 h-32 w-32 bg-[#DD8A1A]"></div>
			<img
				src={founderOne.src}
				alt="Aravind Kumar sitting with children outdoors"
				class="absolute right-0 top-0 h-[82%] w-[88%] object-cover shadow-[18px_18px_0_#111827]"
			/>
			<p class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 max-w-md bg-[#0F766E] p-7 text-3xl font-black uppercase leading-none text-white shadow-[12px_12px_0_#DD8A1A]">
				The first promise was simple: keep coming back.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div>
			<p class="mb-5 text-sm font-black uppercase text-[#0F766E]">How it started</p>
			<h2 class="text-4xl font-black uppercase leading-none text-[#111827] sm:text-6xl">
				A founder story rooted in proximity.
			</h2>
			<div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-lg font-medium leading-8 text-[#1F2937]">
				<p>
					The movement started when learning support became more than a program. It became a weekly act of presence: showing up, learning names and noticing what children needed before asking them to perform.
				</p>
				<p>
					Community mattered because no single classroom could carry the whole weight. Families, mentors, volunteers and neighbors had to become part of the answer.
				</p>
				<p>
					That belief still leads the work: consistency builds trust, and trust gives children room to ask, try, lead and dream out loud.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
